President Trump presented the Presidential Medal of Freedom to Roger Penske, a prominent figure in American industry, entrepreneurship, and auto racing. Penske, the founder of Team Penske, has achieved numerous victories and accolades throughout his career in racing, including winning the Indianapolis 500 a record-breaking 18 times. He is also a successful businessman, heading an automotive empire that employs over 64,000 people. In addition to his accomplishments in racing and business, Penske has made significant philanthropic contributions, particularly in Detroit. The ceremony was attended by Vice President Mike Pence, members of the Cabinet, and Penske's family.